-- Saudi British Bank May Sell Dollar Bonds; Meets Investors From November 4
-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2010-11-01T13:01:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/saudi-british-bank-may-sell-dollar-bonds-after-investor-meetings.html
Saudi British Bank, the lender 40
percent owned by HSBC Holdings Plc, said it may sell dollar
bonds after meeting investors from Nov. 4.  The bank is in the process of arranging meetings with fixed
income investors in Europe, the Middle East and Asia, Saudi
British said in a statement to the bourse today. The bond sale
will be subject to market conditions, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
